==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|ymagerie}}, from {{der|en|frm|imagerie}}; equivalent to {{af|en|image|-ry}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈɪmɪd͡ʒɹi/|/-ədʒɹi/|/ˈɪmɪd͡ʒəɹi/}}
** {{audio|en|en-us-imagery.ogg|a=US}}
* {{IPA|en|/ɪˈmedʒ(ə)ri/|a=Indic}}

===Noun===
{{wp}}
{{en-noun|~}}

# The work of one who makes [[image]]s or visible representation of objects.
# [[imitation|Imitation]] work.
# Images [[in general]], or [[en masse]].
# {{lb|en|figuratively}} Unreal show; imitation; appearance.
# The work of the imagination or fancy; false ideas; [[imaginary]] [[phantasm]]s.
# [[rhetorical|Rhetorical]] decoration in writing or speaking; vivid descriptions presenting or suggesting images of sensible objects; figures in discourse.

